| 1708 || || Legislation || || The {{w|Foreign Protestants Naturalization Act 1708}} is passed, allowing for the naturalisation of French Protestants ({{w|Huguenot}}s) who had fled to Britain since the {{w|Edict of Fontainebleau}}.
